An ordinary walk home from school turns into an epic journey for Usato. After suddenly being dropped into another world with two fellow students, Usato learns he was summoned there by accident. But things turn around when he discovers a unique aptitude for healing magic! Now, he trains beyond human limitations, using his self-healing abilities to gain absurd strength and unrivaled stamina.
(Source: Crunchyroll)

Nearly a century after magic was recognized as a real form of technology, Miyuki Shiba begins her term at Magic High School. An honor student, she dreamed of enjoying school with her older brother Tatsuya, an irregular student. But a rift between the gifted Course 1 students and the inferior Course 2 students could stand in the way. This time, Miyuki is the star of the show!
(Source: Funimation)

Twenty-four-year-old Koduka Chiyo quit her job and is wallowing in self-pity in her apartment. Shes also three months behind on her rent. Then her landlady proposes an unusual solution: have sex with her, and shell help with the debt, the filthy apartment, and the loneliness driving Chiyo to beer and escapism. After a one-night stand, the two women decide to keep up the arrangement. Their growing relationship leads to questions of identity, getting ones life together, and if something tender can develop from an arrangement that started with a bang.
(Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)
<i>Notes: - Chapter count includes 1 extra. - Nominated for the Tsugimanga 2020 Award in the Manga Category.<i>
Ashita, Watashi wa Dareka no Kanojo

"One time a week, I will be the girlfriend of [someone]." A bitter love story depicting the realities of love between female college students who earn money on behalf of her and men attracted by her. The first volume is a young office worker who rents the protagonist snow as a fake girlfriend, and draws a distorted love pattern of sota and snow. A substitute girl who plays the customer and the woman of their ideals to the end... Is the distance between two people's mind really close?
<i>Nominated for the Tsugimanga 2020 Award in the Web Manga Category.<i>
